“'''雨中的泪水'''”（{{lang-en|'''Tears in Rain'''}}），也被称为'''C光束演说'''（{{lang-en|'''C-Beams Speech'''}}）<ref>{{cite DVD notes|type=Commentary Track|others=[[Ridley_Scott|Ridley Scott]]|origyear=1982|title=''[[Blade_Runner|Blade Runner: The Final Cut]]''|year=2007|publisher=[[Warner_Bros.|Warner Bros.]]}}</ref>是电影《[[银翼杀手|银翼杀手]]》中的最后[[獨角戲|独白]]，由人造人罗伊·巴蒂（{{lang-en|Roy Batty}}）讲述，由[[鲁特格尔·哈尔|鲁特格尔·哈尔]]饰演。最终呈现在大银幕上的这段话不是原来剧本中的，在很大程度上是演员哈尔在拍摄前夜即兴创作的<ref>{{citation |title=Ridley Scott: interviews |author=Ridley Scott, Paul Sammon  |page=103 | publisher=University Press of Mississippi |year=2005}}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=0_c17KnrLvMC&pg=PA204 |title=Type Idea Index |author=Jim Krause |page=204 |year=2006 |isbn=9781581808063 |access-date=2014-05-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106011352/https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=0_c17KnrLvMC&pg=PA204 |archive-date=2017-01-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。这段独白已经作为“也许是电影史上最动人的死前独白”<ref>{{citation |title=The philosopher at the end of the universe |author=Mark Rowlands |year=2003 |quote=Roy then dies, and in perhaps the most moving death soliloquy in cinematic history... |pages=234–235}}</ref>进入了流行文化中，经常作为科幻作品的代表被引用<ref>{{citation |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=pmioTTM-SDcC&pg=PT163 |title=Different engines |author=Mark Brake, Neil Hook |page=163 |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |year=2008 |isbn=9780230553972 |bibcode=1988SciAm.259f.111E |volume=259 |journal=Scientific American |doi=10.1038/scientificamerican1288-111 |issue=6}}</ref> 。

{{cquote|{{lang-en|I've seen things you people wouldn't believe. Attack ships on fire off the shoulder of Orion. I watched C-beams glitter in the dark near the Tannhäuser Gate. All those moments will be lost in time, like tears in rain. Time to die.}}}}
（我曾见过你们人类难以置信的东西。战舰在[[獵戶座|獵戶座]]的肩端之外燃烧。我看见了C光束在汤豪泽之門附近的黑暗中闪烁。所有這些時刻都將消逝在时间里，就像雨中的淚水。死的时候到了。）

鲁特格尔·哈尔在拍摄现场表演该段对话时，电影工作人员集体鼓掌，有些人甚至当场哭了。2000年，英国的《[[观察家报|观察家报]]》将这段对话评选为电影史上十大经典时刻的第六位<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2000/feb/06/top-10-film-moments-usual-suspects-psycho |journal=[[The_Observer|The Observer]] |title=The top 10 film moments - 6: Blade Runner — Batty's dying speech in the rain |date=2000-02-06 |accessdate=2014-10-06}}</ref>。

鲁特格尔·哈尔在自传中提到只不过将原本的剧本对话剪切为几行，增加了“所有这些时刻都将消逝在时间里，就像雨中的泪水。”早期的一个版本为<ref>{{Citation|author=Rutger Hauer|author2=Patrick Quinlan|last-author-amp=yes|date=2007
 |title=All Those Moments: Stories of Heroes, Villains, Replicants and Blade Runners|publisher=[[HarperEntertainment|HarperEntertainment]]|isbn=978-0-06-113389-3
}}</ref>：

{{cquote|{{lang-en|I have known adventures, seen places you people will never see, I've been Offworld and back...frontiers! I've stood on the back deck of a blinker bound for the Plutition Camps with sweat in my eyes watching the stars fight on the shoulder of Orion. I've felt wind in my hair, riding test boats off the black galaxies and seen an attack fleet burn like a match and disappear. I've seen it...felt it!}}}}

